==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pasque
<hw>Pasque</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>pasque</ets>.]</ety> <def>See <er>Pasch</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pasque flower</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a name of
several plants of the genus <gen>Anemone</gen>, section
<gen>Pulsatilla</gen>. They are perennial herbs with rather large
purplish blossoms, which appear in early spring, or about Easter, whence
the common name. Called also <altname>campana</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pasquil</ent>⟦br⟧
